text: Kunakbayevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Nikolayevsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 105 as of 2010. There is one street. == Geography == It is located 19 km from Sterlitamak, 14 km from Nikolayevka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Kunakbayevo, Sterlitamaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
